The paper deals with image processing and machine learning techniques for change detection, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of heuristics and the development of new architectures also suggest a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of annotated data, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the mention of large scale Earth observation systems suggests a possible connection to neural networks for environmental monitoring (cs.NE).
